This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Plea/sentencing hearing on January 5, 2023 at 11:00 am.
Money posted on 7/12/22 prior to 2022CM1455 being created.  Per poster $500.00 has been moved to this case.

COURT TO USE THE $1000.00 ALREADY ON DEPOSIT; DEFENDANT WILL NEED TO POST AN ADDITIONAL $500.00.

Defendant to comply with I.D. Processing. Absolute sobriety, defendant is not to possess or consume any alcohol. Defendant is not to enter any premises, other than a grocery store, that sells/serves alcohol beverages by the drink or into any liquor store. Defendant is not to use/possess any controlled substances without a valid prescription and take as prescribed. Defendant not to possess any drug paraphernalia. The defendant is ordered to comply with CAM monitoring and drug testing through WCS.  CAM duration and drug testing frequency pursuant to Pretrial Supervision Program protocols. 9:59 AM; Case called for Hearing.  Defendant Andrew S Jakubowski in court.  Prosecuting attorney Shawn N Woller in court for the State of Wisconsin. Atty. Luis Gutierrez appears as a friend of the Court on behalf of the defendant.  Court notes at the last hearing the defendant went to WCS to pay to have the result re-tested and the Court has received the results and they were still positive.  Atty. Gutierrez presents statements and notes his client still states he was not using.  Atty. Gutierrez is asking the court take no action with respect to bail and is asking the matter be set over for plea and sentencing in about 45-60 days.  Court inquires if the defendant is employed.  Defendant advises he has been working at Cosco since last week.  Based on the WCS non-compliance the Court orders cash bail increased to $1500.00 in this case ONLY, defendant will need to post an additional $500.00, and all previously set conditions will remain the same.  Court will adjourn for projected plea and sentencing in about 60-90 days.
